---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import CoverageChecker from "../../components/CoverageChecker.jsx";
import fundamentals from "../../data/fundamentals.json";

const covered = (fundamentals.companies || []).map((c) => c.ticker).join(", ");
---

<BaseLayout title="Can it pay its interest? — Owner Scorecard">
  <p class="back"><a href="/tools">← Tools</a></p>

  <header class="hero">
    <h1>Can it pay its interest?</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      One ratio, computed from the latest annual filing: a year of operating profit
      divided by the interest bill. Below 1× and the company didn't earn enough to
      pay its lenders — the rest came from refinancing, asset sales, or someone's
      patience.
    </p>
  </header>

  <CoverageChecker client:visible />

  <h2>How to read it</h2>
  <ul class="method">
    <li><strong>Operating income (EBIT)</strong> is profit from the business before interest and tax — what's actually available to pay lenders.</li>
    <li><strong>Interest expense</strong> is the annual cost of carrying the debt.</li>
    <li>Their ratio is <strong>times interest earned</strong>. 1× means the whole year's operating profit went to interest and nothing else.</li>
    <li>Graham wanted a real margin of safety here — coverage many times over, holding up across a full cycle, not just in the good year. A common distillation of his bond tests is ~5×; a reference line, not a law.</li>
    <li>High coverage says <em>solvent</em>, not <em>cheap</em>. It rules a company out, or keeps it in the game — it doesn't tell you what to pay.</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="note">
    Covered so far: {covered}. The universe expands over time; the figures come from
    SEC EDGAR XBRL filings, and every result links to the filing it came from.
  </p>

  <style>
    .back { margin: 0 0 10px; }
    .hero h1 { margin: 0 0 6px; }
    .lede { color: #333; margin: 0; }
    h2 { border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding-bottom: 4px; margin-top: 26px; }
    .method { padding-left: 18px; }
    .method li { margin: 8px 0; }
    .note { font-size: 13px; color: #555; margin-top: 18px; }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
